WorldStage Newsonline– The Roving Team of the Federal Operations Unit, Zone C of the Nigeria Customs Service (NCS), Owerri has confirmed the seizure of  a container carrying military hard wears along Aba- Port Harcourt road. According to a statement, the container was taken to Owerri where proper examination was carried out in the presence of the representative of the Owner which revealed 11 bales containing new sets of sawn military camouflage. Each bale contain 400 pairs of sawn military camouflage; 15 cartons containing Altama combat boots. Each carton contains 20 pears; some sacks of made up garment; seven wooden furniture kitchen cabinets; 337 packs of new foreign tiles. Made in China; 27 medical equipment. Made in china; 34 rolls of water hose. Made in China; some household items. Comptroller in charge of FOU, Zone C, Ahmed Azarema was quoted as saying that  the owner’s  representative had been detained while investigation to get all those connected to this criminality has already commenced.